HEADWORD: Saxicava
<hw>Sax`i*ca"va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>saxicavas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Saxicavae</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See <er>Saxicavous</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of marine bivalve shells of the
genus <gen>Saxicava</gen>. Some of the species are noted for their power
of boring holes in limestone and similar rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

